      <h1 class="txtThin">Privacy Policy</h1>
      <h5>Effective as of May 23, 2018</h5>
      <h5>Version 4.0 updated as of March 3, 2021</h5>
      <h5>Version 5.0 updated as of August 10, 2021</h5>

      <h4>1. NOTICE</h4>
      <p>uTest, a service of Applause App Quality, Inc. ("uTest," “we,” “us” and “our”), has created this privacy statement in order to demonstrate our firm commitment to privacy. The following discloses the information gathering and dissemination practices for this Web site uTest.com. This privacy statement covers the collection, treatment and use of any personal information gathered by uTest from our testers and visitors to our websites (hereafter referred to as “you”, “your”, “tester”). This privacy statement does not apply to third parties and their actions that we do not own or control, including, but not limited to, any third party websites, services and applications that you elect to access through our websites.</p>
      <p><b>Information collected from website visitors</b></p>
      <p>For each visitor to our web site, our web server automatically recognizes only the user's IP address, but not the e-mail address. We collect only the IP address, but not the e-mail address, of visitors to our website, aggregate information on what pages users access or visit, and information volunteered by the user, such as survey information and/or site registrations.</p>
      <p>The information we collect is used to provide you with and improve the content of our website. The information we collect is not shared with other third party organizations for their own commercial purposes.</p>
      <p><b>Information collected from testers</b></p>
      <p>When you register on and further use services provided through our website, we request certain information. Except for information which you provide in your profile or in connection with testing projects, we do not share any of your personally identifiable or transactional information with any person or entity. By providing your profile information or participating in any testing project, you acknowledge and agree that we may share such information with Applause Customers and other Members as we deem necessary for operational purposes. uTest is not intended for use by participants under the age of 13. To the extent any such users under age 13 participate in uTest, we obtain verifiable parental consent in compliance with applicable law.</p>
      <p>uTest will only collect certain biometric information upon notice and signed written informed consent on a case by case basis solely in the event such tester may voluntarily choose to participate in a certain testing cycle requiring such information.</p>
      <p>We will never sell, share or rent your information to any third-parties or marketing firms.</p>
      <p>If you supply us with your postal address online you will only receive the information for which you provided us your address.</p>
      <p>When visiting ours or any client's website and signing up for or using our services through any Service Page, you may choose to supply us with information that identifies users personally. For Testers, this information may include name and contact information, gender, birth date, postal code, occupation and industry, shipping and billing information, behavior patterns, purchase history, and other information.</p>
      <p>The information you provide is used to:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Determine your eligibility for testing projects</li>
        <li>Contact you about your participation in testing projects</li>
        <li>Identify your articles, form posts, comments and other contributions on uTest.com</li>
        <li>Other information</li>
      </ul>
<br>
      <p>We collect non-identifying, general, generic and aggregate information to better design our web site and services. We may share the aggregate data with other third parties. With respect to security: uTest.com uses PayPal, which utilizes industry-standard encryption technologies when transferring and receiving Company and transaction data exchanged with our site.</p>


      <h4>2. CHOICE</h4>
      <p>From time to time, we may change our privacy policy. If our information practices change at some time in the future we will post the policy changes to our website to notify you of these changes. If you are concerned about how your information is used, you should periodically check back at our website.</p>
      <p>Except as set out in this policy, we will provide you with notice and give you the right to opt out if your personal information is to be disclosed to a new third party controller or to be used for a purpose materially different from the purpose for which it was originally collected or subsequently authorized by you. </p>
      <p>We acknowledge that EU and Swiss individuals (as well as California residents) have the right to access the personal information/data that we maintain about them. To the extent you cannot correct any information by updating your uTest profile, we will provide you with access to and/or the opportunity to correct all information that we maintain about you upon your request. Please direct your request to <a href="mailto:privacydpo@applause.com">privacydpo@applause.com</a>. We will respond to you within the time period required by applicable laws, and in any event within 45 days of receiving your request.</p>



      <h4>3. ONWARD TRANSFER</h4>
      <p>Only those third parties which are set out in this Privacy Policy, or with whom you have transactions will receive your information.</p>
      <p>We may be required to transfer and disclose information, including personal information, in response to lawful requests by public and governmental authorities and law enforcement agencies, including to meet national security or law enforcement requirements. We may also disclose your information (i) with our affiliates, (ii) service providers, (iii) if we are required to do so by law; (iv) if we believe that it is necessary to enforce or apply our terms of use and other agreements or otherwise protect and defend the rights, property or safety of Applause or that of our customers; (v) in order to comply with a judicial proceeding, court order or other legal obligation or government inquiry; or (v) to any entity that acquires any part of Applause’s current operations by way of merger, de-merger, acquisition, reorganization or sale of assets, or (vi) Community Project Managers and Test Team Leads for administering testing projects. We may potentially be liable under the Privacy Shield Principles if a third party processes personal information in a way inconsistent with those Principles, unless we prove we are not responsible for the event giving rise to the damage.</p>



      <h4>4. DATA TRANSFERS – EU-US, GDPR AND SWISS-US PRIVACY SHIELD FRAMEWORK</h4>
      <p>The Information that we collect from you may be transferred to, and stored at, a destination outside of your country and the European Economic Area ("EEA") and, in particular, the US, which may have different or less protective privacy laws than those in your country.</p>
      <p>The protection of personal data is important to us. We process personal data only in accordance with the applicable data protection requirements, in particular the General Data Protection Regulation (GDPR), as well as the EU-US Privacy Shield and the Swiss-US Privacy Shield Program to best protect the transfer of personal data from European Economic Area, Switzerland and the UK to the US and other third party countries. As a general business practice, we enter into Data Protection Agreements and other terms and conditions that incorporate by reference the Standard Contractual Clauses adopted by the European Commission as between Applause and our vendors and subprocessors.</p>
      <p>uTest complies with the EU-US Privacy Shield Framework and the Swiss-US Privacy Shield Framework as set forth by the US Department of Commerce regarding the collection, use, and retention of personal information.  uTest has certified that it adheres to the Privacy Shield Principles of Notice, Choice, Accountability for Onward Transfer, Security, Data Integrity and Purpose Limitation, Access, and Recourse, Enforcement and Liability. If there is any conflict between the policies in this privacy policy and the Privacy Shield Principles, the Privacy Shield Principles shall govern. To learn more about the Privacy Shield program, and to view our certification page, please visit <a href="https://www.privacyshield.gov/">https://www.privacyshield.gov/</a>. With respect to personal data transferred pursuant to the EU-US and Swiss-US Privacy Shield Framework, uTest is subject to the investigatory and enforcement powers of the U.S. Federal Trade Commission.</p>
      <p>uTest commits to resolve complaints about your privacy and our collection or use of your personal information. Where you have a complaint regarding our collection, storage, or use of your personal information, you may make a complaint to uTest via email to privacydpo@applause.com or via mail to 100 Pennsylvania Ave., Framingham, MA 01701.</p>
      <p>We will respond to you within 45 days of receiving your request. </p>
      <p>uTest has further committed to refer unresolved privacy complaints under the EU-US and Swiss-US Privacy Shield Principles to BBB EU PRIVACY SHIELD, a non-profit alternative dispute resolution provider located in the United States and operated by the Council of Better Business Bureaus. If you do not receive timely acknowledgment of your complaint, or if your complaint is not satisfactorily addressed, please visit <a href="https://bbbprograms.org/programs/all-programs/bbb-eu-privacy-shield-consumers/ProcessForConsumers/">www.bbbprograms.org/programs/all-programs/bbb-eu-privacy-shield-consumers/ProcessForConsumers</a> for more information and to file a complaint. </p>
      <p>uTest complies with the General Data Protection Regulation (GDPR) as applicable to our business. See Exhibit 1: “<a href="https://prod-utestv2.s3.amazonaws.com/2021/03/03/18/09/11/937a268f-1aca-4204-951a-11e7824ba411/DataProtectionInformationuTestMarch2021.pdf" target="_blank">Data Protection Information uTest</a>”
      </p><p>Please note that if your complaint is not resolved through these channels, under limited circumstances, a binding arbitration option may be available before a Privacy Shield Panel.</p>



      <h4>5. ADDITIONAL INFORMATION FOR CALIFORNIA RESIDENTS</h4>
      <p>California law requires that we disclose certain information regarding the categories of Personal Information” (PI) we collect. For purposes of this policy, PI has the meaning provided by the California Consumer Privacy Act (CCPA) and does not include information that is publicly available, that is deidentified or aggregated such that it is not capable of being associated with us, or that is excluded from the CCPA’s scope, such as PI covered by certain sector-specific privacy laws, such as the HIPAA, the FCRA, GLBA or the Driver's Privacy Protection Act of 1994. This CA Notice does not apply to information relating to our employees, contractors, or other personnel.</p>
      <p><b>For purposes of the CCPA, Applause has not sold PI relating to California (CA) residents in the last 12 months.</b></p>
      <h5>I. Collection and use of PI</h5>
<br>
      <p>A. We collect PI from and about CA consumers for a variety of purposes as set forth in Section B.</p>
      <p>B. For California residents, the type of PI we collect will depend on how you engage with us (for example, as a customer or potential customer, or as a website visitor). In the last 12 months, we have collected the following categories of PI generally:</p>
      <ul>
          <li>Identifiers, such as your name, address, phone number, email address, or other similar identifiers</li>
          <li>California customer records, such as payment information</li>
          <li>Professional and educational information, if you apply for a job or project with us through our website</li>
          <li>Commercial information, such as a history of our services purchased, obtained or considered</li>
          <li>Internet/Network information, such as device information, logs and analytics data;</li>
          <li>Geolocation data, such as precise location data from your device or generated based on your IP address; and</li>
          <li>Inferences about your interests and preferences, generated from your voluntary site use</li>
       </ul>
<br>
     <p>C. We collect this information directly from you, from our business partners and affiliates, from your browser or device when you visit our website, www.utest.com, or from third parties that you permit to share information with us.</p>
     <p>D. For detailed information about the PI collected, please see  Exhibit 1 as referenced in Section 4.</p>
 <h5>II. Disclosure of PI</h5>
<br>
      <p>A. We share PI with third parties for business purposes. The categories of third parties to whom we disclose your PI may include:</p>
      <ul>
          <li>our service providers and advisors</li>
          <li>vendors who assist us with marketing and advertising our services</li>
          <li>analytics providers such as Google</li>
          <li>third parties, including customers, with your consent or at your direction, or with whom you interact through for our testing services</li>
      </ul>
<br>
      <p> B. When we disclose your PI to our service providers, vendors or other third parties that process the information on our behalf, we have entered into a written contract that includes terms substantially similar to this notice and we will remain liable for any breach of this notice that is caused by the acts or omissions of our service providers.</p>
      <p>C. We do not sell your PI for monetary or other valuable consideration. For more detail on how your PI may be processed, please see Exhibit 1 as referenced in Section 4.</p>

 <h5>III. Rights and Choices</h5>
<br>
      <p>A. As a California resident, you may exercise the following rights:</p>
      <ul>
          <li>The Right to Know any or all of the following information relating to your PI we have collected and disclosed in the last 12 months, upon verification of your identity:</li>
               <ul>
